76561197979085978,Recommended,494150,29183721,Posted: 11 January,all,Vekaol,"Really enjoying this! Mechanics are getting better and better with each update and the feel of boxing is pretty realistic. You can do jabs, uppercuts, hooks and straight punches (also body shots) and there actually is quite a nice amount strategy involved in using different attacks as well between different opponents.I like the dodging and defending mechanisms. Blocking straights, hooks and body shots really require you to actively switch the hand positions and even though the headset is kind of ""heavy"", using head movement to dodge really works nicely as well. I can't comment much on the movement and leg work since I have limited space so that is important part of real boxing strategy which I can't test really well. This game does require quite a big space fully enjoy it, but even almost stationary boxing still works ok.There is a nice amount of variance between the opponent styles and their strategies also have been getting better with updates. Although maybe they are bit oo repetetive as after a while you might find some strategy which works kind of too well against them. But you can still add some challenge by just mixing your own game up a bit and not exploit the ""sure"" strategy.I didn't like having unblockable punches with one of the opponents. In the latest beta update his punches are now blockable and I find it much more enjoyable while still challenging. Although maybe unblockable punches would make for a nice mini game on top of the zombies and headless opponent. I did find that trying to use only dodging required a hefty amount of energy and it was a really nice workout!Overall, I feel this game captures the feel of boxing really well even at this stage while it seems that updates are still frequent. I hope the game keeps evolving in the future as well!"
