,Recommended,494150,29061458,Posted: 6 January,all,Diabolic,"While not a simulation game, it's the closest thing in development at the moment. It's early access and still needs some work to be truly great, but it's already fun. It is steadily getting updates and getting improved gameplay.This game will give you a good workout, especially if you aproach it like real boxing and move around and throw some decent punches. While not a simulation you will be doing all the same movements as you would in real life (assuming you put effort into it) so it's like an intense shadow boxing session. You don't need to be fit to play the game though and you can also play more casually.If you're interested in VR boxing I'd recomend this game, and you'll be getting a decent  workout while playing. Also while not exactly promised the dev is interested in adding multiplayer, so if that interests you it will probably be added at some point. There are some complaints I but I think the dev is working on most of them. Things also mentioned by others, like the punch force cap, which dev has said will be raised.Extended: Using new Beta.The game is getting better and better, it's now a much more authentic boxing experience, for the experienced boxers, let's not call it a sim, but it is a true boxing game now in my opinion. Power cap has been removed, opponents move more naturally and fight more dynamically. You can get flash KOs and one punch knockdowns. You can also be taken out very quickly yourself, so you have to think about what you're doing.The game mechanics have been tightened up so it feel a lot more real now, and it's more challenging, although it might still be easy for some (very few) people. You now get blurry vision when damaged which convey the damage really well, and is a good reprentation of being wobbled. Still no rounds but that is coming, and then it will be even better. There are more positives that I can't think of right now."
