,Recommended,494150,24365301,"Posted: 16 July, 2016",all,AnthonyFransella,"Review as of Update 2 (Lightning Luis just added):Ok so this is obviously an early access game, so there isn't that much content. With that said, what there is seems to be pretty good. Full disclosure: I used to do full contact fighting, sorta like MMA but before that became a specific thing, and used at different times boxing gloves and juijitsu gloves. Overall things feel pretty good. You hold the controllers in a way that makes sense for this context. The opponents are really easy, but it gives you a little workout since they block just about everything unless they're hitting or about to hit.There isn't that much of a sense of actually making contact though, outside the sound. I dunno if it's the shading/lighting or what but it's hard to tell if I landed something (the lack of animation on impact has this effect as well). Body shots don't get any response unless they KO the guy, but the guys KO with the same animation as if you clocked him on the jaw. The characters aren't the most realistic looking, their physiques are kinda weirdly shapes, but it's good enough. I think the dev should look into the NVidia funhouse demo where you punch the little wackamole kind of things. They felt much more real to hit due to their physics and reactions.I would like to see things like hit counts, %'s, some kind of indication of whether I'm hitting hard or soft (just base this off velocity I guess?), and better detection of whether the guy is actually blocking my strikes. Basically I'd like that as the player becomes a better boxer all around he's rewarded. If I can throw 200+ fast jabs/round, and target them through his guard, that'd be nice to get rewarded for. The motivation would be there to become genuinely stronger/faster, so you can overcome the tougher opponents. That'd be truly unique."
